This has been a pet project of mine for a while. I inherited this leather from my grandfather. It was tanned by Hutterites that lived near my grandfather. They naturally tan this cowhide, which gives it the look and feel of buckskin. The leather had flaws; bug bites, scars, scratches, and brands. But I feel like it adds to the story. It’s not often I make something for myself, but I’m excited to have these in my shop.
